  "text": "(ω 0 ,0) does not belong to H 1 per,e ([0, L]) (because it is odd), we conclude that G (ω 0 ,0) is one-to-one. A simple analysis also shows that G (ω 0 ,0) is also surjective (see, for instance, [CITATION_1] Theorem 3.2] ). As consequence of the Implicit Function Theorem we establish the desired result.",
